
1. PROJECT OVERVIEW
-------------------
token.pe is an on-chain data visualization tool designed to analyze 
the profitability of DeFi protocols using classic financial metrics, 
specifically the P/E (Price-to-Earnings) ratio. It allows users to 
compare market valuation (Mcap/FDV) against the actual revenue 
generated by the protocols.

2. INTERFACE STRUCTURE
----------------------
The interface is divided into two main sections (tabs):

A. "Compare" Tab:
   - An interactive token selector (chips) to filter the display.
   - Three dynamic charts:
     - P/E Ratio: Historical relative valuation.
     - Rolling 30d Revenue: Cumulative revenue over the last 30 days.
     - Daily Revenue: Detailed daily revenue (bar chart format).
   - Global and individual time filters (7d, 1m, 3m, 6m, 1y).

B. "Table" Tab:
   - A comprehensive list of protocols with real-time data:
     - Mcap & FDV (including a progress bar for the circulating ratio).
     - 24h Price Change.
     - Revenue (30d and Annualized).
     - Financial Ratios: P/E and FDV/E.
   - Column-based sorting system.
   - Automatic valuation analysis (Cheap, Fair, Expensive).
   - Detailed per-protocol view (accordion) displaying a mixed 
     Price/PE Ratio chart with a "Buy Zones" toggle.

3. DATA SOURCES & TECHNOLOGIES
------------------------------
- Data: CoinGecko API (Price/Mcap) and DefiLlama API (Revenue).
- Charts: Chart.js (v4.4.1) with the annotation plugin.
- Design: "Parchment" theme (vintage paper/cream aesthetic) using 
  'EB Garamond' for serif text and 'DM Mono' for numerical data.
- Layout: Modern HTML5/CSS3 utilizing Flexbox and "sticky" 
  elements for seamless navigation.

4. CALCULATION LOGIC
--------------------
- Ann. Rev. (Annualized Revenue) = Last 30 days revenue × 12.
- P/E (Price-to-Earnings) = Market Cap / Annualized Revenue.
- FDV/E = Fully Diluted Valuation / Annualized Revenue.
- Percentiles: "Buy Zones" are calculated based on the 20th and 80th 
  percentiles of the historical P/E ratio over a one-year period.
